{
  "texts": [
    "(TRF i,CPU i) TRF i CPU iIn our previous work [46], we applied a Support Vector Regression (SVR) based approach to estimate VNFs needs in term of CPU as a function of the processed traffic.",
    "We explained that studying the behavior of a VNF as a function of its environment helps modeling its resource requirements and favors its dynamic allocation.",
    "The SVR model was trained using a dataset provided by [47], composed of pairs, where is a vector describing the entering traffic, and is the amount of CPU used by the VNF to process the traffic.",
    "Experimental results showed the efficiency of the SVR model and superiority over a neural network based solution.An interesting recent contribution is proposed in [48,53] where the authors designed ENVI, an elastic VNF resource allocation scheme.",
    "ENVI uses neural network (NN) model to detect resource flexing events (increase or decrease of resource requirements) during the VNF chain lifetime."
  ]
}